   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER SEVENTY-SIX TESTIMONIES BY THE SAINTS</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND WORDS OF EXHORTATION CHURCH MEETING</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Date:Evening, May 8, 1948</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Place:Hardoon Road, Shanghai</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Note:Testimonies by all the brothers and sisters who have handed over themselves.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>At the end of the meeting, Brother Nee gave a word of exhortation.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Brother Nee: For over twenty years, God has been taking the way of recovery among us.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>This way is becoming clearer and clearer.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Today, everyone who holds back anything for himself is either a sad person or a weeping person.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Within the last few days, I have met some of the happiest people I have ever seen.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Many people held my hands tightly, and they were both excited and happy.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Praise God, there are many happy faces here today.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>They have all handed themselves wholeheartedly to the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Tonight, it is as if the last train is about to leave.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>I hope that no one will miss this train and that no one will be left behind.</S>
   </TEXT>
  </BODY>
